{{TProblem |
You see a body lying across the road and need to stop.
If your vehicle was initially traveling at 100 km/h and skids to a stop on a 2.5% upgrade, taking 75 m to do so,  what was the coefficient of friction on this surface?
}}

* [[Fundamentals of Transportation/Sight Distance/Solution|Solution]]

[[Category:Fundamentals of Transportation Problems]]

{{TProblem |
You see a a body lying across the road and need to stop.
If your vehicle was initially traveling at 100 km/h and skids to a stop on a 2.5% upgrade, taking 75 m to do so,  what was the coefficient of friction on this surface?
}}

{{Answer |
<math>
d_b  = \frac{{\left( {100*\left( {\frac{{1000}}{{3600}}} \right)} \right)^2  - \left( 0 \right)^2 }}{{2*\left( {9.8} \right)*\left( {f + 0.025} \right)}} = 75m
\,\!</math>

<math>
\left( {f + 0.025} \right) = \frac{{\left( {27.78} \right)^2 }}{{2*\left( {9.8} \right)*75}}
\,\!</math>

<math>
f = 0.50
\,\!</math>
}}

[[Category:Fundamentals of Transportation Solutions]]

