{{Query|6 years after being created this book still has no content}}
This is a manual to assist businesses in recovering from various network outages. Some of the steps in the process involve coordination with various governmental agencies.

== Table of contents ==
#Introduction
#Inventory all Software with vendor address & phone number, version, cost,location of media,  installed configuration
#Inventory all Hardware with vendor address & phone number, complete H/W specs, any configuration such as RAID, cost and location
#Create a LAN diagram of Routers, Switches, Servers, and wiring
#Document the existing backup activities including location of backups
#Specify a DR team and disseminate their contact information
#Identify recovery procedures for various levels of outages-power, H/W, LAN, Internet, etc.

